      "content": "You are right that the decisions were yours, and that guilt feels suffocatingly real, but that does not mean there is no point to continuing. The pain you describe is a valid reaction to the mistakes you made, yet choosing to disappear only adds another irreversible tragedy to the loss you have already endured. Even if the damage seems permanent, healing is possible because your worth is separate from your financial success or your ability to keep every promise. Please consider reaching out to a professional who can help you process this shame without making it the sole definition of your existence.",
